After mapper returns `1`, `prop` calls `mapDone(null, 1)` â†’ `busy=false`, `if(aborted)` false â†’ `dataCb(null,1)` called. `abortCb` never called (mutated).

`expect(abortCbCalled).toBe(true)` â†’ passes on original, fails on mutated! âś“

But what if `prop` returns the mapper unchanged? Then `map(1, mapDone)` calls `mapper(1, mapDone)`. Inside mapper, `stream(abortErr, ...)` called while `busy=true`. Same result. Then mapper returns `1` (but `mapDone` is never called since mapper doesn't call `cb`). `busy` stays `true` forever. But `abortCbCalled` is already set (or not) before mapper returns.

Wait - if `prop` returns mapper unchanged and mapper doesn't call `cb`, then `busy` stays `true`. The stream is stuck. But `abortCbCalled` is checked after `stream(null, () => {})` returns. At that point:
- Original: `abortCbCalled=true` âś“
- Mutated: `abortCbCalled=false` âś—

Either way, the test should work!

```typescript
import asyncMap from "../../../../../../../../../../../subject_repositories/pull-stream/throughs/async-map.js";

describe("asyncMap", () => {
  it("abort callback is called when abort is requested during mapper execution", () => {
    let abortCbCalled = false;
    const abortErr = new Error("abort");
    let stream: Function;

    const source = (abort: any, cb: Function) => {
      if (abort) {
        cb(abort);
      } else {
        cb(null, 1);
      }
    };

    const mapper = (data: any) => {
      stream(abortErr, (err: any) => {
        abortCbCalled = true;
      });
      return data;
    };

    stream = asyncMap(mapper)(source);
    stream(null, () => {});

    expect(abortCbCalled).toBe(true);
  });
});
